            <p>The CSS Working Group has a document online of “…Mistakes in the Design of CSS”, one of them is this:</p>
<p>“Flexbox should have been less crazy about flex-basis vs 
width/height. Perhaps: if width/height is auto, use flex-basis; 
otherwise, stick with width/height as an inflexible size. (This also 
makes min/max width/height behavior fall out of the generic 
definition.)”</p>
<p>Can you talk about what they mean by this?</p>

