        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Grant</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-555673"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2013-09-22T07:44:56+00:00">September 22, 2013</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Flexbox is what CSS has been sorely lacking since its 
inception – an easy way to create flexible web page layouts without the 
need for floats, clears, margin: 0 auto and JS hacks. I look forward to 
the day when flexbox is supported by a big enough share of the browser 
market to put into this all of our production sites.</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=555673#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-555673", "555673", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to Grant">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

