    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-1544695">

      <div class="grid group comment-wrap" id="comment-1544695">

        <div class="comment-avatar grid-1-5">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c59b3876d77c49fae5e615dec5d9c582?s=160&amp;d=retro&amp;r=pg" width="50" height="50">
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Stuart</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1544695"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2014-04-09T01:32:42+00:00">April 9, 2014</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>This really annoyed me and was broken for a bit, so I 
wanted to share in case anyone ever comes across this in the future. If 
you need to support blackberry 7+, make sure you use</p>
<p><code>-webkit-box-orient: vertical;<br>
    -moz-box-orient: vertical;<br>
    -webkit-box-direction: normal;<br>
    -moz-box-direction: normal;<br>
    -webkit-flex-direction: column;<br>
    -ms-flex-direction: column;<br>
    flex-direction: column;</code></p>
<p>…if you use row wrap, it doesn’t wrap and just puts everything 
side-by-side. Also, very important. Make sure the child elements of the 
parent flex container don’t have <code>display: inline;</code> applied to them. It breaks it for some reason. I hope this helps someone!</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=1544695#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1544695", "1544695", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to Stuart">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    
  <ul class="children">

    <li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-1563853">

      <div class="grid group comment-wrap" id="comment-1563853">

        <div class="comment-avatar grid-1-5">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c59b3876d77c49fae5e615dec5d9c582?s=160&amp;d=retro&amp;r=pg" width="50" height="50">
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Stuart</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1563853"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2014-04-12T03:16:05+00:00">April 12, 2014</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>One last important thing to remember if you have to support blackberry 7+…make sure all child elements have <code>float:none</code> applied to them…if floats are applied, they’ll just not appear. I hope this helps!</p>

            <div class="reply">
