    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-1580733">

      <div class="grid group comment-wrap" id="comment-1580733">

        <div class="comment-avatar grid-1-5">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2c9af39c37d449912420962911729a3f?s=160&amp;d=retro&amp;r=pg" width="50" height="50">
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Guilherme Bruzzi</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1580733"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2014-05-04T23:23:59+00:00">May 4, 2014</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Hi Chris! Very nice article! But the last example 
“mobile-first 3-columns layout with full-width header and footer” in my 
34.0.1847.131 chrome didn’t make the two sidebars half of the size of 
the main content.<br>
I had to write:<br>
    @media all and (min-width: 800px) {<br>
      .aside-1 { order: 1; flex: 1 25%; }<br>
      .main    { order: 2; flex: 2 1 50%; }<br>
      .aside-2 { order: 3; flex: 1 25%; }<br>
      .footer  { order: 4; }<br>
    }<br>
On the last media query in order to do that ( <a href="http://cdpn.io/rhbmd" title="codepen link" rel="nofollow">http://cdpn.io/rhbmd</a> ).</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=1580733#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1580733", "1580733", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to Guilherme Bruzzi">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

