    <li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-1581192">

      <div class="grid group comment-wrap" id="comment-1581192">

        <div class="comment-avatar grid-1-5">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f3cff47e29ce10ed9f20b59d96f8508c?s=160&amp;d=retro&amp;r=pg" width="50" height="50">
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Ry</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1581192"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2014-05-14T10:19:45+00:00">May 14, 2014</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Great guide, nice update! Has always been very useful.</p>
<p>One thing I’ve noticed missing (here and almost every other flexbox guide) is how to do flex-grow and flex-shrink in IE10.</p>
<p>flex-grow<br>
<code>-ms-flex-positive:;</code></p>
<p>flex-shrink<br>
<code>-ms-flex-negative:;</code></p>
<p>Would be great to have this footnoted somewhere.</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=1581192#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1581192", "1581192", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to Ry">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    
