          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Yehuda</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1583835"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2014-07-16T13:24:34+00:00">July 16, 2014</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>try align-content: flex-start; on the container. I’m not too sure if it will help for your purpose, but with your demo it works.<br>
Also, I would rather set flex: 1 1 20%; on each sub item instead of 
specifying the width (again, it depends on what you want to do).</p>

