      <div class="grid group comment-wrap" id="comment-1584625">

        <div class="comment-avatar grid-1-5">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/905a339246b4f5170dbd8749b6769be9?s=160&amp;d=retro&amp;r=pg" width="50" height="50">
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Fredrik</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1584625"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2014-08-22T01:51:05+00:00">August 22, 2014</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I’ve been experimenting with <code>flex-wrap</code> recently, and found that Safari doesn’t support it (on desktop or mobile), although it claims to, ie. <code>Modernizr.flexwrap</code> is true. I’ve <a href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/issues/1414" rel="nofollow">filed a bug report with Modernizr</a>
 for this. Wanted to spread the word, since there seems to be some 
confusion around this property flying around in the wake of Firefox 
previously not having supported it.</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=1584625#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1584625", "1584625", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to Fredrik">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

