          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">coolcat007</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1586127"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2014-10-21T16:14:02+00:00">October 21, 2014</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I kind of agree with the article. Both Flexbox and Grid 
layout have their pro’s and cons. The flexbox is more suitable for 
dynamic content (think about displaying a random amount of images of a 
random size), where the grid layout is preferable for known content 
areas. Both can adjust for the screensize, but are optimized for 
different applications.</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=1586127#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1586127", "1586127", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to coolcat007">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

