        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Jared Proske</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1592030"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2015-01-20T16:18:21+00:00">January 20, 2015</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>Your first example at this link (<a href="http://codepen.io/HugoGiraudel/pen/LklCv" rel="nofollow">http://codepen.io/HugoGiraudel/pen/LklCv</a>)
 does not work in IE 11. IE doesn’t seem to like -webkit-flex-flow. 
Adding  flex-wrap:wrap;  flex-direction: row; or just flex-flow: row 
wrap; works though.</p>

