        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Chris Coyier</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1593303"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2015-03-20T08:06:37+00:00">March 20, 2015</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>When you change the flex direction, you’re changing the main axis. That’s how I think about it anyway. Flex-direction:</p>
<blockquote><p>
  establishes the main-axis
</p></blockquote>

