    <li class="comment byuser comment-author-launchoverit odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-1593464">

      <div class="grid group comment-wrap" id="comment-1593464">

        <div class="comment-avatar grid-1-5">
          <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" class="lazyload-gravatar" alt="User Avatar" data-src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/90aa2a3a916d063a8f4e65d62324914c?s=160&amp;d=retro&amp;r=pg" width="50" height="50">
        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">launchoverit</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1593464"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2015-03-27T11:00:55+00:00">March 27, 2015</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>I’m new to flexbox and certainly don’t want to spread my noob confusion, but I noticed a couple things:<br>
 * Regarding this image – <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/images/rel-vs-abs-flex.svg" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/images/rel-vs-abs-flex.svg</a>.
 Initially I thought this was super helpful. However, when I looked at 
where it’s used in the w3 spec, it doesn’t actually talk about using 
“auto” as a value for flex-basis at all (just a value for the “flex” 
shorthand), it just has it in the image for some reason – <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-property" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-property</a><br>
 * Then I found this section of the spec, and it looks like using “auto” as a value for flex-basis is in debate – <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-basis-property" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-flexbox/#flex-basis-property</a></p>
<p>Questions:<br>
 * Should we avoid using “flex-basis:auto” for the time being? And if so, should there be a note accompanying that image?<br>
 * Am I right in thinking that the w3 spec is a bit 
confusing/disorganized in those places? Worthy of me sending a 
comment/email to somebody?</p>
<p>Lastly: Very, very greatful for this post. Thanks!</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=1593464#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1593464", "1593464", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to launchoverit">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

