        </div>

        <div class="comment-body group grid-4-5">

          <div class="comment-author-wrap vcard">
            <div class="comment-author">Kp</div> <div class="comment-time"><a href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/#comment-1596444"><span class="screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</a> <time datetime="2015-08-17T16:24:19+00:00">August 17, 2015</time></div>
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="comment-content">

            <p>In the event anybody is having issues getting it to work on firefox for the 2nd example (tomato background)</p>
<p>Put the flex items into their own container with no other element in them.<br>
Add * flex-flow: row wrap; * to .flex-container</p>
<p>Hope this helps.</p>

            <div class="reply">
              <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/?replytocom=1596444#respond" onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-1596444", "1596444", "respond", "21059" )' aria-label="Reply to Kp">Reply ↓</a>            </div><!-- .reply -->

