            <p>@Louisa You didn’t include your CSS code, so it’s impossible to tell what’s wrong. I put your HTML into a Pen and set  <code>#page1conteneur { display: flex; }</code>and it works fine.</p>
<p>If you want help, you need to post your CSS code as well. Better yet, post your question and all related code to a site like <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/" rel="nofollow">Stack Overflow</a> that’s designed for questions and answers</p>
<p>Here’s my example. I replaced the images with images from <a href="http://lorempixel.com/" rel="nofollow">LoremPixel</a> just to give me something to look at. …</p>
<p>(Editor: this demo started 404ing, it must have been deleted.)</p>

